  "Question": "<p>Prove <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_620\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"a^{n}+1\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <msup> <mi>a</mi> <mi>n</mi> </msup> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </math></span> is divisible by <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_621\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"a+1\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>a</mi> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </math></span> if <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_622\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"n\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>n</mi> </math></span> is odd:</p> <p>We know <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_623\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"a\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>a</mi> </math></span> cannot be <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_624\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"-1\" display=\"inline\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mo>-</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </math></span> and the <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_625\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"n\\in\\mathbb{N}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2208</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\mathbb</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>N</mi> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span>. Since <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_626\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"n\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>n</mi> </math></span> must be odd, we can rewrite <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_627\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"n\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>n</mi> </math></span> as <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_628\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"2k+1\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>k</mi> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </math></span>. Now we assume it holds for prove that it holds for the next term.</p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_629\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"a^{2(k+1)+1}+1\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <msup> <mi>a</mi> <mrow> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <mi>k</mi> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </msup> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </math></span> <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_630\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"=a^{2k+3}+1\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi></mi> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <msup> <mi>a</mi> <mrow> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>k</mi> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mn>3</mn> </mrow> </msup> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span> <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_631\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"=a^{3}\\cdot a^{2k}+1\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi></mi> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <mrow> <msup> <mi>a</mi> <mn>3</mn> </msup> <mo>\u22c5</mo> <msup> <mi>a</mi> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>k</mi> </mrow> </msup> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span> <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_632\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"=(a^{3}+1)\\cdot a^{2k}-a^{2k}+1\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi></mi> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <mrow> <mrow> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <msup> <mi>a</mi> <mn>3</mn> </msup> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> <mo>\u22c5</mo> <msup> <mi>a</mi> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>k</mi> </mrow> </msup> </mrow> <mo>-</mo> <msup> <mi>a</mi> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>k</mi> </mrow> </msup> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span></p> <p>Im not sure on what to do next. Since <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_633\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"a^{2k}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <msup> <mi>a</mi> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>k</mi> </mrow> </msup> </math></span> means that the exponential term will be even and thus you cant use the fact that <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_634\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"a^{n}+1\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <msup> <mi>a</mi> <mi>n</mi> </msup> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </math></span> is divisible by <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_635\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"a+1\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>a</mi> <mo>+</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </math></span> if <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_636\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"n\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>n</mi> </math></span> is odd.    </p>",
